"use strict";(self["webpackChunklola_workshops"]=self["webpackChunklola_workshops"]||[]).push([[39],{3742:function(e,t,n){n.r(t),n.d(t,{default:function(){return u}});var a=n(6768),i=n(3904),o=n(3813),r=n(6756),l=n(5526);function s(e,t){return(0,a.uX)(),(0,a.Wv)(o.I,null,{default:(0,a.k6)((()=>[(0,a.bF)(r.L,{class:"mt-10"},{default:(0,a.k6)((()=>[(0,a.bF)(l.B,{cols:"12"},{default:(0,a.k6)((()=>[t[1]||(t[1]=(0,a.Lk)("h1",{class:"text-center"},"Behaviour Policy",-1)),(0,a.bF)(i.J,{class:"my-10 pa-7"},{default:(0,a.k6)((()=>t[0]||(t[0]=[(0,a.Lk)("p",{class:"font-weight-bold"},"Policies",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," We lead an inclusive environment which welcomes children who want to learn about art. There are many students that come from all sorts of backgrounds and they are all treated equally. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," There are three behaviours of concern that will not be tolerated in the LoLA Creative Space ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," 1) Poor physical behaviour. Examples can include but are not limited to flicking paint, throwing items, pulling hair, tripping other students or teachers, kicking, threatening physically any other student or member of staff, etc. These physical behaviours and any similar behaviours not mentioned, will or can result in termination of the contract to provide art lessons. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," 2) LoLA creates an atmosphere of learning and everyone is expected to contribute positively to that atmosphere for the enjoyment of everyone. Not following the advice or guidance of the art leader and showing them disrespect in front of other students can result in non-admittance to the art club. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," 3) Children need to respect the equipment and classroom. Taking care of equipment such as brushes and pencils, desks and chairs, and walls. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," Unacceptable behaviour of any kind is the judgement of the art teacher, and they exercise their judgement for the benefit of everyone equally. We expect to have discussed issues such as the above with the parent or guardian who is expected to have listened and taken any concerns seriously. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," If or when a service contract is cancelled or terminated by us, any remaining unused service will be refunded ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",{class:"underline"},"Child Safeguarding Policy",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," This policy is for children at school or up to 18 years old and does not apply to adults.This policy should be read alongside Lots of Lovely Art’s terms and conditions. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," All children and young people have the same protection regardless of age, disability, gender, racial heritage, religious belief, sexual orientation or identity. The policy was developed with reference to NSPCC guidelines, who see child welfare as paramount, as enshrined in The Children Act 1989. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," Lots of Lovely Art delivers stimulating tutoring for children that requires a reasonable degree of calm and an atmosphere within which the majority can concentrate within a group session. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," LoLA aims to retain the atmosphere for the safety and comfort of all attendees equally and will raise any concerns initially with the child, and if problems persist, with parents or carers. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," Children are required to be left in the art club for the duration. Delaying leaving by more than a couple of minutes or returning before the appointed finish time, is not allowed for the reason of safety for all children - unless by prior arrangement which can be verbally arranged on the day. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," Children will be working in an open plan shared space, and parents can expect no child to be isolated in the normal course of events. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," Parents can expect art teachers and art assistants (‘staff’) to be hands-off children, for example when welcoming children to the club or saying goodbye. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," Children are tutored on an individual basis and this one to one discussion will be held in the club at a table shared by other children. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," We expect a mobile phone number to be able to call the parent at any time during the club session. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," All Lots of Lovely Art teachers and any individuals aged 16+ assisting are DBS enhanced checked. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",{class:"underline"},"Social Media",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," We frequently celebrate children’s art by taking photographs or videos and posting them to the Lots of Lovely Art Instagram and Facebook page. We will endeavour not to include faces in the photography but if you would specifically not like your child to be photographed please let us know by emailing hello@lotsoflovelyart.com ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",{class:"underline"},"Drop off/ pick up Children",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," At or under Year 4, children will be expected to be accompanied by their parent within the LoLA Creative Space for the duration of the workshop and will also be expected to pick up their child from the workshop area promptly. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," We will not knowingly allow a child at or under Year 6 to walk out of the space without the parent acknowledging with the staff that the pupil is safely in their care. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," Elder siblings or grandparents of the pupil can take the child if and only if the parent confirms with the art leader in writing (by email or text) in advance. If these arrangements are sprung on staff without prior arrangement, and the child gives any cause for concern, we will expect the parent to answer the nominated phone number that we have on record. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," If after about 30 minutes, that phone is not answered and there is still concern, we may keep the child safe in our care until such time as we can work out what’s happening. This may include taking the child to a safe place not in the art club or driving them home. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",{class:"underline"},"Toilet facilities",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," We plan for it to be very rare to need the toilet because the sessions are only 1hr to 1.5 hrs, because pupils love art, we don’t want to waste time. To minimise these occurrences, we encourage parents to prepare the pupils in advance of each session. If a visit to the bathroom is required, staff will normally direct or guide pupils, but on no occasion can they assist in any way. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," It is expected that visits to the toilet will be an exception, but if it becomes regular, (regular being once each on two or three consecutive sessions), we will inform the parent and discuss. If a child becomes sick as in vomiting, we will call the parent immediately. ",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",{class:"underline"},"Medical conditions",-1),(0,a.Lk)("p",null," Staff do not administer routine medication as a rule. If this is required, please discuss with the staff. Even after discussion, if staff have concerns, they have the right to refuse entry and defer discussion for a calmer time period, in which case a catch up session will be offered in line with our terms and conditions. Some children carry EpiPens for allergic reaction. Please make the staff aware and provide all guidance required on the assumption that the art leader knows nothing. Normally, these EpiPens can be accommodated, but the date of medicines and the medicines being full- are the responsibility of the parent. The LoLA space will hold a basic first aid kit. ",-1)]))),_:1})])),_:1})])),_:1})])),_:1})}var h=n(1241);const c={},d=(0,h.A)(c,[["render",s]]);var u=d}}]);
